Privacy Policy for Anyscor - Amateur Sports Platform
Effective date: 23/07/2023
At Anyscor, we are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. This Privacy Policy outlines how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your data when you access and use our amateur sports platform, including our website and mobile applications (collectively referred to as “Anyscor”).
By accessing and using Anyscor, you agree to the terms and practices described in this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with any part of this policy, please refrain from using our platform.
Information We Collect:
1.1 Personal Information: When you use Anyscor, we may collect personal information that can identify you directly or indirectly, such as your name, email address, profile picture, and other contact details.
1.2 Sports Data: We collect and display live scores and results for various amateur sports events. This information may include team/player names, match schedules, scores, and related sports data.
1.3 Usage Information: We gather non-personal information about your interactions with Anyscor, such as your IP address, device information, browser type, and operating system, for statistical and analytical purposes.
How We Use Your Information:
2.1 Providing Services: We use the information collected to deliver and improve our services, including displaying live sports scores, schedules, and results to the public.
2.2 Communication: We may use your contact details to respond to your inquiries, send updates about Anyscor, and provide relevant information about amateur sports events.
2.3 Personalization: With your consent, we may use your information to personalize your experience on Anyscor, such as showing content based on your preferences.
2.4 Analytics: We utilize non-personal information for internal purposes, such as analysing user behaviour, troubleshooting technical issues, and improving the platform’s performance.
2.5 Legal Compliance: In certain situations, we may be required to use and disclose personal information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal proceedings.
Data Sharing and Disclosure:
3.1 Third-Party Partners: We may share non-personal information with third-party partners for marketing, analytics, or other purposes. However, we will not disclose your personal information to these parties without your explicit consent.
3.2 Legal Requirements: We may disclose your information if required by law or if we believe in good faith that such action is necessary to comply with legal obligations or protect the rights, safety, or security of Anyscor, its users, or others.
Data Security:
4.1 Protection Measures: We employ reasonable technical and organizational measures to safeguard your personal information from unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, or destruction.
4.2 Data Retention: We will retain your information only for as long as necessary to fulfil the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy or as required by law.
Children’s Privacy:
Anyscor is not intended for individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us, and we will promptly delete such data.
Third-Party Links:
Anyscor may contain links to external websites or services that are not controlled by us. This Privacy Policy does not apply to such third-party platforms. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of these third-party websites or services before providing any personal information.
Your Choices:
You have the right to access, modify, or delete your personal information held by Anyscor. If you wish to exercise any of these rights or have concerns about your data, please contact us at hello@anyscor.ie.
Changes to this Privacy Policy:
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will revise the “Effective date” at the top of this policy. We encourage you to review this policy periodically to stay informed about how we collect, use, and protect your data.
Contact Us:
If you have any questions, concerns, or suggestions regarding this Privacy Policy or Anyscor’s data practices, please contact us at hello@anyscor.ie.
This Privacy Policy is governed by the laws of Ireland without regard to its conflicts of law principles.
Last updated: 23/07/2023
